<br>
I have found LdoN to be wonderful. It is a lot of what many people have been crying for.<br>
<br>
1) Very group oriented, you will learn teamwork if you are to be successful.<br>
2) Goods and Bads don’t suffer because they don’t have certain classes.<br>
3) Good loot can be gotten over time with out having to be on huge raids.<br>
4) Every one gets points towards loot that they can get personally.<br>
5) No trains from other groups.<br>
6) No farmers taking all the mobs you need.<br>
7) All classes are useful.<br>
8) You don’t have to invest great big chunks of time to accomplish some thing.<br>
9) XP is pretty good and the plat isn’t bad either.<br>
10) They are fun, exciting and you have a goal rather than just seeing how long you can grind XP.<br>
<br>
Sure it isn’t perfect but it is pretty damned good. After a few bad ones I have been on fairly consistent successes. Some important things you can do to improve the chances of success.<br>
<br>
Plan what you are going to do. Who is MA, who will ML. Every one should know their roll. Every one should know they stop to roll on No Drop Augments. Every one should know how they need to move, what contingencies you think you might see and what should be done.<br>
<br>
Take the time to prep before you take the mission and then be fully prepped before you enter the dungeon.<br>
<br>
Once you hit the dungeon, shoot and scoot. You should move together, quickly and smoothly as a unit to cut down on pull time. You should be communicating on when to move, mana levels, pacifying and general combat spam. <br>
<br>
When you are done sell, pay for regents and split. Every one comes out a winner.<br>
<br>
I think LDoN is great. Yea the level thing is a pain but it makes for very well set levels on the dungeons. Looking for a good group can be a pain but it encourages people to look for groups, on blue servers with their populations it probably isn’t such a problem. LDs can suck “Oh well”. You will need to be able to work well as a group if you are to be regularly successful at these dungeons.<br>
